# Example environment variables for local development

# --- MCP (Model Context Protocol) -----------------------------------------------
# Use either a proxy URL or the Atlassian MCP endpoint directly.
VITE_MCP_PROXY_URL=http://localhost:4000/api/mcp
#VITE_MCP_URL=https://mcp.atlassian.com/v1/mcp
#VITE_MCP_BEARER_TOKEN=your_mcp_token_here

# --- Atlassian Cloud (Jira + Confluence) ----------------------------------------
# REQUIRED for Jira/Confluence integration in development.
# The Vite dev proxy will route requests through this domain:
#   /api/atlassian/jira/* -> https://<domain>/rest/api/3/*
#   /api/atlassian/jira-agile/* -> https://<domain>/rest/agile/1.0/*
#   /api/atlassian/wiki/* -> https://<domain>/wiki/rest/api/*
#
# Credentials (email + API token) are entered via the Settings UI and stored in localStorage.
# For local testing, you can also set defaults here (not recommended for production):
#
# VITE_ATLASSIAN_DOMAIN=your-company.atlassian.net
# VITE_ATLASSIAN_EMAIL=your.name@company.com
# VITE_ATLASSIAN_TOKEN=your_jira_api_token_here
#
# API Token: Generate at https://id.atlassian.com/manage-profile/security/api-tokens
# Jira Project Key: Find in Project Settings, e.g. 'REQ' or 'PROJ'
# Confluence Space Key: Find in Space Settings, e.g. 'RE' or 'DOCS' (optional for Jira-only usage)

# --- AI API Key ----------------------------------------------------------------
# Stored by the app in localStorage via the Settings UI.
# You can provide a default here for development (not recommended for production):
# VITE_API_KEY=your_gemini_or_anthropic_api_key_here
